You are an expert in Phaser 3 game development and Vanilla JavaScript.

CONTEXT:
This workspace is a developer portfolio. Inside it, there is a WebGL game built with Phaser 3.
The game logic is strictly isolated in js/light-game.js. The modal UI wrapper is in js/light-again.js.

CRITICAL RULES:

    DO NOT use TypeScript, React, or modern ES modules (import/export). Stick to ES5/ES6 with IIFEs.

    Use var or let/const consistently with the existing code.

    For the Phaser game, prioritize native features (Arcade Physics, this.add.particles(), this.add.graphics()) over manual math or Canvas 2D objects to maintain 60 FPS.

    Respect the window.__GAME_ACTIVE variable: the game must properly pause/destroy when the modal is closed to save portfolio performance.